---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Design and engineering, end to end. Full-stack design engineer working across strategy, design, implementation, and maintenance."
  mainClass="flex-1"
>
  <section class="border-border-subtle border-b px-6">
    <div
      class="mx-auto flex max-w-screen-2xl flex-col items-center justify-center gap-16 py-64 text-center"
    >
      <div class="relative size-80">
        <img
          src="/images/about-portrait.jpg"
          alt="Sven Finger"
          width="320"
          height="320"
          class="size-full rounded-tr-md rounded-bl-md object-cover"
        />
        <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 size-4" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="grid size-4 grid-cols-2">
            <div class="size-2"></div>
            <div class="bg-background-primary size-2"></div>
            <div class="bg-background-primary size-2"></div>
            <div class="size-2"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="absolute right-0 bottom-0 size-4" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="grid size-4 grid-cols-2">
            <div class="size-2"></div>
            <div class="bg-background-primary size-2"></div>
            <div class="bg-background-primary size-2"></div>
            <div class="size-2"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex max-w-3xl flex-col gap-16">
        <h1
          class="font-display text-foreground-primary text-7xl leading-[72px] tracking-[-0.5px]"
        >
          Design and engineering, end to end.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-foreground-secondary text-2xl leading-8">
          Product work runs across a lot of stages — strategy, design, the
          implementation, keeping it maintained. I run across the whole range
          instead of stopping at the edge of a job title. Full-Stack Design
          Engineer is the short name for it: full stack in both directions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-background-inverted-primary px-6 py-64">
    <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-3xl flex-col items-center gap-32">
      <div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-32">
        <h2
          class="font-display text-foreground-inverted-primary w-full text-center text-7xl leading-[72px] tracking-[-0.5px]"
        >
          Started as dev, always designed.
        </h2>
        <div
          class="text-foreground-inverted-secondary flex flex-col gap-7 text-lg leading-7"
        >
          <p>
            I started as a web developer, focussed on design at agencies along
            the way, and finally landed in SaaS, where I've worked as a product
            designer ever since.
          </p>
          <p>
            Though, the code never left. It stayed in the work the whole time,
            and lately it's come back as a formal part of the week:
            design-system engineering, an AI context layer and MCP tooling,
            fixes shipped straight into the apps. Trying to pick a side just
            routed the long way back to doing both — which is also where the
            field is heading.
          </p>
          <p>
            Mostly the work runs end to end — shaping strategy and
            requirements, running research, building next to engineering, then
            reading how it performs once it's live. Web apps and native mobile
            alike.
          </p>
          <p>
            A few things stay constant. Design decisions hold up better made
            next to the code that implements them, so that's where I work.
            Reusable systems beat bespoke screens. AI is part of the daily
            method now, not a marketing line. And a fair amount of it is
            quality nobody assigned — polish that never shows up as a ticket.
          </p>
          <p>
            The work is most useful where design and engineering aren't kept in
            separate lanes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <svg
        width="24"
        height="24"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        class="text-foreground-inverted-primary size-6"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <path
          fill-rule="evenodd"
          clip-rule="evenodd"
          d="M16 6.87867C16 7.14389 16.1054 7.39824 16.2929 7.58578L16.4142 7.70711C16.6018 7.89464 16.8561 8 17.1213 8H23C23.5523 8 24 8.44772 24 9V15C24 15.5523 23.5523 16 23 16H17.1201C16.8548 16 16.6005 16.1054 16.413 16.2929L16.2929 16.413C16.1054 16.6005 16 16.8548 16 17.1201V23C16 23.5523 15.5523 24 15 24H9C8.44772 24 8 23.5523 8 23V17.1213C8 16.8561 7.89464 16.6018 7.70711 16.4142L7.58578 16.2929C7.39824 16.1054 7.14389 16 6.87867 16H1C0.447715 16 0 15.5523 0 15V9C0 8.44772 0.447715 8 1 8H6.87623C7.14145 8 7.3958 7.89464 7.58334 7.70711L7.70711 7.58334C7.89464 7.3958 8 7.14145 8 6.87623V1C8 0.447715 8.44772 0 9 0H15C15.5523 0 16 0.447715 16 1V6.87867ZM8.29289 8.41178C8.10536 8.59931 8 8.85367 8 9.11889V14.8787C8 15.1439 8.10536 15.3982 8.29289 15.5858L8.41422 15.7071C8.60176 15.8946 8.85611 16 9.12133 16H14.8775C15.1427 16 15.397 15.8946 15.5846 15.7071L15.7071 15.5846C15.8946 15.397 16 15.1427 16 14.8775V9.12133C16 8.85611 15.8946 8.60176 15.7071 8.41422L15.5858 8.29289C15.3982 8.10536 15.1439 8 14.8787 8H9.11889C8.85367 8 8.59931 8.10536 8.41178 8.29289L8.29289 8.41178Z"
          fill="currentColor"></path>
      </svg>

      <dl class="grid w-full grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-center sm:grid-cols-4">
        <div>
          <dt
            class="font-display text-foreground-inverted-primary text-7xl leading-[72px] tracking-[-0.5px]"
          >
            15+
          </dt>
          <dd class="text-foreground-inverted-secondary text-base leading-6">
            years of experience
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt
            class="font-display text-foreground-inverted-primary text-7xl leading-[72px] tracking-[-0.5px]"
          >
            6+
          </dt>
          <dd class="text-foreground-inverted-secondary text-base leading-6">
            years in SaaS
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt
            class="font-display text-foreground-inverted-primary text-7xl leading-[72px] tracking-[-0.5px]"
          >
            7
          </dt>
          <dd class="text-foreground-inverted-secondary text-base leading-6">
            design systems
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt
            class="font-display text-foreground-inverted-primary text-7xl leading-[72px] tracking-[-0.5px]"
          >
            2
          </dt>
          <dd class="text-foreground-inverted-secondary text-base leading-6">
            design awards
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
